Package: estDLVM
Type: Package
Title: Discrete latent variable models estimation through different versions of the EM and the VEM algorithms
Version: 1.0
Date: 2022-08-22
Authors@R: c(
  person("Luca", "Brusa", email = "luca.brusa@unimib.it", role = c("cre", "aut")),
  person("Fulvia", "Pennoni"),
  person("Francesco", "Bartolucci"))
Description: The estDLVM package provides efficient functions for performing maximum likelihood and approximate maximum likelihood estimation in the context of discrete latent variable models. The package is implemented in C++ to ensure superior efficiency in computations. For the latent class and the hidden Markov models, the package offers three versions of the expectation-maximization algorithm: standard (EM), tempered (TEM), and evolutionary (EEM). Notably, the standard EM implementation for latent class models relies on the MultiLIRT package, while for hidden Markov models, it builds upon the LMest package. For the stochastic block model, the package offers two versions of the variational expectation-maximization algorithm: standard (VEM) and evolutionary (EVEM). 
